## Sample Interview Flow

### Part 1: Introduction (10 mins)
- Interviewer introduction
- Candidate/stakeholder background
- Overview of GRACE platform
- Agenda review

### Part 2: Technical Deep Dive (30 mins)
- Technical questions based on role
- Problem-solving scenarios
- System design discussions

### Part 3: Behavioral/Situational (15 mins)
- Past experience with governance
- Handling conflicts or challenges
- Communication skills assessment

### Part 4: Q&A (5 mins)
- Candidate questions
- Next steps
- Timeline

## Evaluation Criteria

### Technical Skills (40%)
- Understanding of governance concepts
- System design capabilities
- Security knowledge
- Compliance framework familiarity

### Problem-Solving (30%)
- Analytical thinking
- Creativity in solutions
- Practical approach
- Trade-off awareness

### Communication (20%)
- Clarity of explanations
- Active listening
- Stakeholder management
- Documentation skills

### Cultural Fit (10%)
- Alignment with company values
- Collaboration approach
- Growth mindset
- Ownership mentality

## Red Flags to Watch For

❌ Lack of security awareness
❌ No experience with compliance frameworks
❌ Poor communication skills
❌ Over-engineering simple solutions
❌ Inability to explain trade-offs
❌ No questions about the role/company

## Follow-up Actions

After interview:
1. Debrief with interview panel within 24 hours
2. Complete scorecard and submit feedback
3. Check references for top candidates
4. Extend offer or provide feedback to recruiter

